---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Data Deletion Request - ReguMe" 
  description="Request deletion of your ReguMe account and personal data."
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Data Deletion Request</h1>

    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      You have the right to delete your account and all associated data at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Delete Your Data</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Option 1: In-App (Recommended)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Open the ReguMe app</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
        <li>Tap <strong>"Account"</strong></li>
        <li>Tap <strong>"Delete Account"</strong></li>
        <li>Confirm deletion</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>All your data will be permanently deleted within 30 days.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">Option 2: Email Request</h3>
      <p>If you cannot access the app, email us at:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@regume.com">privacy@regume.com</a><br/>
        <strong>Subject:</strong> Data Deletion Request
      </p>
      
      <p><strong>Include in your email:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your registered email address</li>
        <li>Your account username (if known)</li>
        <li>Confirmation that you want all data deleted</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p><strong>We will respond within 30 days.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <h2>What Gets Deleted</h2>

    <p>When you delete your account:</p>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Personal information (email, name, demographics)</li>
      <li>Saved protocols and routines</li>
      <li>Tracking data and check-ins</li>
      <li>Preferences and settings</li>
      <li>Account access credentials</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What Remains (Anonymized)</h2>

    <p>Some data cannot be deleted because it's anonymized and cannot be linked back to you:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Aggregated analytics (no personal identifiers)</li>
      <li>Anonymized outcome insights</li>
      <li>System logs (retained for 90 days for security purposes)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      This anonymized data helps us improve ReguMe for all users and cannot be traced back to you.
    </p>

    <h2>Deletion Timeline</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <ul style="list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;">
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;"><strong>Request received:</strong> Immediate confirmation email</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;"><strong>Data deletion:</strong> Within 30 days</li>
        <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong>Confirmation:</strong> Email sent after deletion completes</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-warning">
      <h3 style="margin-top: 0;">⚠️ Cannot Be Undone</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Data deletion is permanent and cannot be reversed.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        If you create a new account later, it will be treated as a new user with no access to 
        your previous data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Alternative: Export Your Data</h2>

    <p>
      If you want to keep a copy of your data before deleting your account, you can request a 
      data export first:
    </p>

    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:privacy@regume.com">privacy@regume.com</a> with the subject 
      "Data Export Request"
    </p>

    <h2>Questions?</h2>

    <div class="card">
      <p>For questions about data deletion or privacy:</p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@regume.com">privacy@regume.com</a><br/>
        <strong>Response time:</strong> Within 30 days
      </p>
      <p>
        Read our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for more information about how 
        we handle your data.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

